stylometry: Safety stock is the extra inventory purchased by a company to cover the demand of the product between orders delivered.  Like I mentioned in an earlier example, if a company makes their order on a Monday and it is delivered on Thursday, their lead time is 3 days. The safety stock needs to be enough to cover the inventor for those three days. It is important because if there is no inventory during those three days of lead time, then that is three days the company will not be making a profit.  Also, as mentioned earlier there can be unforseeen circumstances during delieveries such as damaged inventory so the safety stock can act as a "cushion" for inventory.
